---
description: Keep repository changes integrated through develop, not main
alwaysApply: true
---

# Branch Workflow

- Treat `develop` as the integration branch for this project.
- Do not merge or push project changes directly to `main` / `master`.
- Feature branches are fine, but they should target `develop` for pull
  requests and merges.
- If a remote rejects direct updates to a protected branch, do not try to
  bypass it. Push a feature branch and target `develop`.
- Before release/versioning work, confirm the current branch and avoid
  preparing release commits from `main` unless the maintainer explicitly
  instructs otherwise.
- Local publishing is different from PR/merge routing: when the user asks to
  publish locally, use the codebase and branch currently checked out unless
  they explicitly ask to switch branches or use the workflow.
